data.name: Honey Garlic Shrimp
data.quickTastyDescription: Succulent shrimp coated in a sweet and tangy honey garlic sauce, served over rice for a delightful meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix honey, soy sauce, and minced garlic.
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp to the skillet and cook until they turn pink, about 2-3 minutes per side.
Pour the honey garlic mixture over the shrimp and cook for another 2-3 minutes until the sauce thickens slightly.
Serve the shrimp over cooked rice and garnish with chopped green onions.
data.detailedName: Honey Garlic Shrimp - A Sweet and Savory Delight
data.modifiersForBase: Sweet honey garlic sauce for added flavor.
